reviews.text: Such a great experience! The environment is very welcoming and enjoyable, with a nice atmosphere all around. The live music made it even more special and set the perfect vibe. Everything was really good, good service and a very pleasant place to spend time. Definitely worth visiting!

I have dined in at the restaurant previously and the outdoor seating area is so beautiful!!
Tonight I ordered through DoorDash but my order was incomplete.
The manager at the restaurant went the extra mile by delivering my two soup orders when DoorDash forgot half my order.
Great customer service and  I loved  the escarole and bean soup. Thank you!

We love Brickhouse in Ridgefield. We come here once a week when we can , if not then bi-weekly. The food is amazing, the people are great.  Ezekiel isn‚Äôt a wonderful host and manager, Sofia is the best waitress . I highly recommend coming here.

I've had the Portuguese pizza twice now and enjoyed it very much. We sat outside and it's very nice. We got there before 6:00 and enjoyed happy hour drinks as well and they have coupons that are big money savers if you join their club. I will to keep coming back.

The food was fine, the service was ok, but the atmosphere was amazing!

I pass this restaurant everyday on my commute and finally came here with my mom on a friday night. It was moderately busy but not fully packed. We sat outside near the fire place. They had a live musician singing and playing guitar which was nice.
The servers seemingly forgot about us and no one came over to take our order. People who were sat after us had their orders taken and drinks served before us. Finally we asked a passing waiter if we could order. The waiter apologized for the oversight and they finally brought some bread for the table and took our order.
We both had glasses of wine which were nice, and ordered a fennel arugula salad and pear, prosciutto and goat cheese pizza to share. The food came out relatively fast, the salad was excellent and very fresh. The pizza was just fine. I was quite excited to try it as Tivoli Pizza, the owners‚Äô other restaurant, is one of my favorite pizza joints in Danbury. The dough was cooked perfectly and had a great charred flavor, but the toppings were lacking. There were big pieces of pear haphazardly thrown on, the goat cheese didn't add much flavor and the prosciutto had more of a ham flavor than I am accustomed to.
We had an affogato for dessert which was also fine, nothing special.
Overall, the food was fine, but their outside space is so stunning it doesn‚Äôt matter. I plan on going back and trying another pizza, hopefully then I could give it 5 stars!

detailedReviews.author: Mari Baci
detailedReviews.text:
The food was fine, the service was ok, but the atmosphere was amazing!

I pass this restaurant everyday on my commute and finally came here with my mom on a friday night. It was moderately busy but not fully packed. We sat outside near the fire place. They had a live musician singing and playing guitar which was nice.
The servers seemingly forgot about us and no one came over to take our order. People who were sat after us had their orders taken and drinks served before us. Finally we asked a passing waiter if we could order. The waiter apologized for the oversight and they finally brought some bread for the table and took our order.
We both had glasses of wine which were nice, and ordered a fennel arugula salad and pear, prosciutto and goat cheese pizza to share. The food came out relatively fast, the salad was excellent and very fresh. The pizza was just fine. I was quite excited to try it as Tivoli Pizza, the owners‚Äô other restaurant, is one of my favorite pizza joints in Danbury. The dough was cooked perfectly and had a great charred flavor, but the toppings were lacking. There were big pieces of pear haphazardly thrown on, the goat cheese didn't add much flavor and the prosciutto had more of a ham flavor than I am accustomed to.
We had an affogato for dessert which was also fine, nothing special.
Overall, the food was fine, but their outside space is so stunning it doesn‚Äôt matter. I plan on going back and trying another pizza, hopefully then I could give it 5 stars!

detailedReviews.text:
Always a great experience when we dine in this restaurant! They have live music, depending on the night, a fireplace and terrace for outdoor dining. In the cold months they have the outside closed off with temporary walls that have large windows to see the terrace. And don‚Äôt worry about being chilly, you won‚Äôt feel that with their high powered heaters at the ceiling, to keep you toasty warm.
Highly recommended but on weekends might need to wait a little bit, but worth it!!!

detailedReviews.author: Paul Shtton
detailedReviews.text: My wife and I are regular visitors to the Brick House, especially for lunches. There is a lovely outdoor seating area, of which a large portion is covered, and thus usable year-round, where we always choose to sit. Service is attentive and friendly, there is a good selection of drinks, and the food is perennially excellent and fair value. The wood-fired pizzas are top-notch; I particularly recommend the Portuguesa artisanal pizza and the Tuscany calzone, but you won't go far wrong with any of the extensive choices on offer.

I can‚Äôt say enough good things about this restaurant! My family and I don‚Äôt review often, but every visit here is an exceptional experience. A special shoutout to Matt, who always goes above and beyond to ensure we have everything we need. He consistently checks on our table, making us feel truly welcomed and cared for.

And the margarita pizza? It‚Äôs to die for! Perfectly cooked with fresh ingredients, it‚Äôs a must-try. Highly recommend this place for both the fantastic food and the outstanding service!
